<p>To add this web app as a standalone application:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Click on the three-dot menu icon in the top-right corner of the browser window.</li>
  <li>From the dropdown menu, select "More tools" and then "Create shortcut".</li>
  <li>In the dialog box that appears, check the "Open as window" option.</li>
  <li>Click the "Create" button.</li>
  <li>The Joy of Rails icon will now be added as a standalone application.</li>
</ol>

<p>Once installed, you can find the web application in your <strong>Start</strong> menu or on your desktop.</p>
